Arch/Manjaro:

sudo pacman -S conky

Fedora:



sudo dnf install conky





---

ğŸ“ 2. Create/Copy a Config File

Conky uses a config file (either .conkyrc or conky.conf).

ğŸ§™â€â™‚ï¸ Option A: Use the Default Example




mkdir -p ~/.config/conky
cp /etc/conky/conky.conf ~/.config/conky/conky.conf




You can now edit it:



nano ~/.config/conky/conky.conf



ğŸ–Œï¸ Option B: Use a Custom Theme

Grab some cool themes:

GitHub: Search â€œConky themesâ€ or â€œConky configsâ€

DeviantArt: Try â€œConky HUD cyberpunkâ€




Example:



